נ רוו ב רו / Those who keep Shabbat enjoy your realm. In addi-
tion to "remembering" (Exodus 20:8) and "keeping" (Deuteronomy 5:12)
the Shabbat, we are also told to "honor and rejoice" in it (Isaiah 58:13).
It would be well if our observance of Shabbat led us to the experience of
honor and delight. While the rabbis spoke of /IToneg shabbat/XX, Sabbath delight,
as referring to bodily pleasures such as eating well, Isaiah spoke of /IToneg
shabbat/XX in connection with his vision for a socially just world. There are
spiritual as well as physical delights of Shabbat to be nurtured and
enjoyed.    /SC/XXR.S.A./XX/PR

